**Î£áµ¢â‚Œâ‚Â³ Iáµ¢,zz Ï‰Ì‡áµ¢ + á¸¢_ctrl = Ï„_dist,z**

This is the **scalar momentum balance** â€” the fundamental constraint the AAMCS must satisfy at all times.

**Key consequence (G-Arbitrage):** If ring i accelerates (Ï‰Ì‡áµ¢ > 0) while ring j decelerates (Ï‰Ì‡â±¼ < 0) such that Iáµ¢ Ï‰Ì‡áµ¢ + Iâ±¼ Ï‰Ì‡â±¼ = 0, then á¸¢_ctrl = 0 â€” no actuator momentum expenditure. This is the mathematical basis of momentum reciprocity.

