Even under the pessimistic scenario ($400/kg launch, 30% market discount, 30% utilization):

**NPV_pessimistic â‰ˆ $740M** â€” still strongly positive.

### E.4 Momentum Reciprocity Savings â€” Quantification

During a G-arbitrage transition where Ring 1 accelerates by Î”Ï‰â‚ while Ring 3 decelerates by Î”Ï‰â‚ƒ:

**Momentum conservation: Iâ‚Î”Ï‰â‚ + Iâ‚ƒÎ”Ï‰â‚ƒ = 0 â†’ Î”Ï‰â‚ = âˆ’(Iâ‚ƒ/Iâ‚)Î”Ï‰â‚ƒ**

Energy change:

**Î”E = Â½Iâ‚(Ï‰â‚+Î”Ï‰â‚)Â² + Â½Iâ‚ƒ(Ï‰â‚ƒ+Î”Ï‰â‚ƒ)Â² âˆ’ Â½Iâ‚Ï‰â‚Â² âˆ’ Â½Iâ‚ƒÏ‰â‚ƒÂ²**

**= Iâ‚Ï‰â‚Î”Ï‰â‚ + Â½Iâ‚Î”Ï‰â‚Â² + Iâ‚ƒÏ‰â‚ƒÎ”Ï‰â‚ƒ + Â½Iâ‚ƒÎ”Ï‰â‚ƒÂ²**

Substituting Î”Ï‰â‚ = âˆ’(Iâ‚ƒ/Iâ‚)Î”Ï‰â‚ƒ:

**Î”E = âˆ’Iâ‚ƒÏ‰â‚Î”Ï‰â‚ƒ + Â½(Iâ‚ƒÂ²/Iâ‚)Î”Ï‰â‚ƒÂ² + Iâ‚ƒÏ‰â‚ƒÎ”Ï‰â‚ƒ + Â½Iâ‚ƒÎ”Ï‰â‚ƒÂ²**

**= Iâ‚ƒ(Ï‰â‚ƒ âˆ’ Ï‰â‚)Î”Ï‰â‚ƒ + Â½Iâ‚ƒÎ”Ï‰â‚ƒÂ²[Iâ‚ƒ/Iâ‚ + 1]**

For Ï‰â‚ƒ > Ï‰â‚ (decelerating the faster outer ring while accelerating the slower inner ring from a lower g-level): Î”E can be **negative** â€” meaning the transition **releases** energy while maintaining total momentum. This released energy is recovered as electrical power via the induction coupling operating in regenerative mode.

**Typical savings per transition:** 35% of single-ring acceleration cost â€” matching the Monte-Carlo estimate cited in Â§7.5.

